1.Functional Component
A functional component is a JavaScript function that returns JSX.

Accepts props as input
Can use React Hooks (like useState, useEffect)
Returns JSX to describe the UI

Example
function Counter() {
  return <h1>Hello</h1>;
}

---------------------------------------------------------------
2.Class Component
A class component in React is a JavaScript class that extends React.Component and 
it is used to create UI components with state and lifecycle methods.

Extends React.Component
Can hold and manage state
Uses lifecycle methods (like componentDidMount)
Returns JSX from the render() method

Example
import React from "react";

class Counter extends React.Component {
  constructor(props) {
    super(props);
    this.state = { count: 0 };
  }

  render() {
    return <h1>Hello</h1>;
  }
}
